  "limitations": [
    "Documentation/declaration pairs are proxy retrieval gold; no model answers were generated or judged.",
    "The primary C metric requires the documented header prototype itself. Retrieving a same-named implementation in a .c file is an exact miss, so symbol-anywhere coverage and top-20 retrieval are reported separately.",
    "C gold derivation is limited to documentation-attached git_* function prototypes; C++ gold derivation keeps documentation-attached named types and callable declarations that the independent adapter can identify reliably.",
    "The two reversed build trials balance order but do not purge operating-system file caches.",
    "The tools retain their native graph schemas and extraction behavior.",
    "The Ravel executable is a working-tree build that still reports v0.2.5, not the published release binary."
